const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Can the AI assess roofs from photos?",
    answer: "A roof photograph shows tile type and general orientation but cannot determine precise azimuth, pitch angle, structural loading capacity, or hidden shading from trees at different times of day. The AI uses the photo constructively — identifying the tile material visible (concrete, clay, slate, flat membrane), noting chimney and dormer positions, and asking about compass orientation and any afternoon shading — building a pre-survey brief that helps you arrive with the correct mounting system and string design assumptions."
  },
  {
    question: "What about multi-message solar threads?",
    answer: "Solar conversations develop across multiple messages — a homeowner sends a roof photo, then confirms south-facing, then mentions they have an EV, then asks about battery brands, then provides their electricity spend, then requests a weekday survey. The AI assembles every fragment into one complete survey lead with the roof image, orientation, EV integration requirement, battery interest, consumption data, and scheduling preference."
